IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: Attachments -NCMEC Cybertips # 160447122, 161288325 Narrative On May 15, 2023, the Maryland State Police Computer Crimes Section /Maryland Internet Crimes Against Children Task Force received NCMEC CyberTips # 160447122, 161288325. The CyberTip, generated by Synchronoss Technologies, indicated that a subject uploading/possessing/distributing child pornography through the internet. The CyberTips were assigned to TFC Burnett for investigation. The CyberTips provided the following information pertaining to the suspect: Cybertip: #160447122 4059058194 TFC Burnett reviewed this CyberTip and observed it to contain one video file depicting child pornography as it is defined by Maryland Law. TFC Burnett conducted a query of the phone number (405-905-8194) and observed it to be registered to Verizon to a River Bard. Through a police search, the phone number may belong to a Allen Joseph Bard (DOB: 11/4/1975), located at 20808 Middlegate Drive, Lexington Park, MD. TFC Burnett authored a subpoena request for the phone number through Verizon which was submitted to the Howard County States Attorneys Office for endorsement. A preservation letter was submitted to Synchronoss Technologies to preserve the suspects account. A search warrant for the suspects Synchronoss Technologies account will be authored. Case Status OPEN / PENDING ADDITIONAL INVESTIGATION
